text:
Twelve KE member members have referred Olga Gerovasilis , Apostolos Gletsos and Kostas Zachariadis to the party’s Ethics Committee for their “extreme” positions.
Specifically, Sofia Inziadou, member of SYRIZA ‘s KE, wrote the following in an online post: “After the extreme positions that were heard recently, a group of comrades from the central committee, approximately 12 people, wanting to express our dissatisfaction and protests, making use of the competent bodies of the party, this morning, we referred Messrs. Gerovasilis, Zachariadis and Gletsos to the Ethics Committee so that it can take charge of the above incidents and do what the statute requires, imposing, if it deems it, the necessary sanctions disciplinary measures. We inform you that three separate files have been submitted, one for each, including electronic files such as video material”.
